--- !u!114 &1810410667
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1810410664}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: edc847c3525e44118a56bf95486e228c, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  description: 'Light probes tell dynamic objects like avatars how to react to your
    baked lighting. Place them closer together where light changes quickly, such
    as near a lamp or a shadow edge. You can keep them spread out in large areas
    where the light stays the same to save on bake times.



    Setting up a grid
    is easier if you drag-select groups of probes in the scene view. You can copy
    and paste these groups to fill a room much faster than placing them one by one.



    Place
    a few probes roughly 50m below your floor or well outside your boundaries. This
    helps avatars with a weird origin point or long accessories like tails. It prevents
    those parts from turning pitch black if they technically clip through the floor
    or sit on the ground.'
  url: 
  locked: 1
  type: 1
