--- !u!114 &2610903513816056033
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 6838085593381728789}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: edc847c3525e44118a56bf95486e228c, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  description: 'For networked buttons, we feed the click event through the toggle
    or button component to the CVR Interactable on the same object using a CustomTrigger.
    The interactable component allows you to drag multiple objects into its array
    list, easier than dragging items there one by one.



    When dragging these
    objects from the hierarchy, remember to click the lock icon in the top right
    of the Inspector. This keeps your button settings visible so you can select and
    drop a whole group of items into the list without the window switching.



    Buffered
    vs. Non-Buffered

    Buffered triggers sync the state for new joiners, ensuring
    they see the same world state as you. Non-buffered triggers only fire for those
    currently in the room.



    When to use which

    Use Buffered for things
    like light switches or doors to prevent desync. Use Non-Buffered for one-time
    events that don''t change the world state, like a sound effect or a quick particle
    burst.'
  url: 
  locked: 1
  type: 1
